.TH SINGINE-SERVER 1 "2026-03-17" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-server \- inspect and query the local Singine HTTP server surface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine server inspect
[\fB--host\fR \fIHOST\fR] [\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB--environment-type\fR \fIlocal|edge|docker\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine server health
[\fB--host\fR \fIHOST\fR] [\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB--timeout\fR \fISECONDS\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine server bridge
[\fB--host\fR \fIHOST\fR] [\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB--action\fR \fIsources|search|entity|sparql\fR]
[\fB--query\fR \fITEXT\fR] [\fB--entity\fR \fIIRI\fR] [\fB--limit\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine server test-case
[\fICASE_ROOT\fR]
[\fB--host\fR \fIHOST\fR]
[\fB--port\fR \fIPORT\fR]
[\fB--logseq-url\fR \fIURL\fR]
[\fB--run\fR]
[\fB--json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B server
command family is the simple local edge interface for Singine.
It reports the default HTTP shape of the Clojure/Camel server and queries the
same endpoints that iOS clients, edge tooling, and Docker-packaged local
services use:
.IP \(bu 2
\fB/health\fR for readiness
.IP \(bu 2
\fB/bridge\fR for SQLite-backed bridge queries
.IP \(bu 2
\fB/cap\fR, \fB/messages\fR, and \fB/timez\fR as the adjacent HTTP surface
.PP
\fBinspect\fR also reports git awareness, Docker packaging, Java interface
paths, activity taxonomy location, and the Ant/SilkPage/xmldoclet publication
pipeline so one command can describe the full Singine architecture boundary.
The Java activity inspection is recursive, so nested packages such as
\fIsingine.activity.photo\fR are included in the reported interface list and in
snapshot output.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B inspect
Show the default host/port profile, environment type, docker files, git branch,
activity taxonomy path, Java interface roots, and migration paths such as
\fI/tmp/sqlite.db\fR and \fI/tmp/singine-xml-matrix\fR.
This is also the quickest way to verify that nested JVM activity packages are
visible before rendering XML/Javadoc publication output.
.TP
.B health
Call \fBGET /health\fR on the configured host/port.
.TP
.B bridge
Call \fBGET /bridge\fR with one of the supported facade actions:
\fIsources\fR, \fIsearch\fR, \fIentity\fR, or \fIsparql\fR.
.TP
.B test-case
Create a self-contained test-case bundle containing:
.IP \(bu 2
a \fBREADME.txt\fR with the exact Singine call sequence
.IP \(bu 2
an \fBactivity.json\fR metadata file
.IP \(bu 2
the default snapshot output path to use
.PP
With \fB--run\fR, also execute the mock unittest case
\fBpy.tests.test_server_surface_commands\fR from the Singine repo root.
.SH DEFAULTS
.TP
.B bind host
\fB0.0.0.0\fR on the JVM server side.
.TP
.B client host
\fB127.0.0.1\fR for local CLI calls.
.TP
.B port
\fB8080\fR.
.TP
.B environment types
\fIlocal\fR, \fIedge\fR, \fIdocker\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine server inspect
singine server inspect --environment-type edge --json
singine server health --json
singine server bridge --action sources --json
singine server bridge --action sparql --query 'SELECT ?s ?p ?o WHERE { ?s ?p ?o } LIMIT 5' --json
singine server test-case /tmp/singine-server-case
singine server test-case /tmp/singine-server-case --run --json
.fi
.SH SIMPLE TEST CASE
The shortest end-to-end Singine-driven surface check is:
.nf
singine server test-case /tmp/singine-server-case
cat /tmp/singine-server-case/README.txt
singine server inspect --json
singine server health --json
singine server bridge --action sources --json
singine logseq inspect --json
singine snapshot save --output /tmp/singine-server-case/snapshot.json --json
python3 -m unittest py.tests.test_server_surface_commands -v
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-bridge (1),
.BR singine-runtime (1),
.BR singine-snapshot (1),
.BR singine-logseq (1)
